<p>Greetings!</p>
<p>We're remaking the character suggestion tag thread, as there are new guidelines for character tags.</p>
<p>Approval is still contingent on 5x3 as usual, however, from here on out, you will need approval from any member of the tech team, JS or higher.</p>
<p>Same deal as before, tell what tag you want added, link the five articles.</p>
<hr />
<h3><span>FAQ</span></h3>
<p><strong>Q. But why? It was so much more efficient!</strong><br />
A. Two reasons. Firstly, a lot of tags weren't getting O5'd. Secondly, there were some suspect characters being added.</p>
<p><strong>Q. JS approving tags?! Are you mad?!</strong><br />
A. Yes.</p>
<p><strong>Q. No seriously you can't trust those scrubs.</strong><br />
A. Totes can, it's a verification step. Also, like, most of the team are mods or something now.</p>
<p><strong>Q. I refuse to let a JS approve my tag.</strong><br />
A. That's not a question, and that's very mean, please leave.</p>
<p>G'luck!</p>

